13 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
14 SECTION 1. NEW LAW A new section of law to be codified
15 in the Oklahoma Statutes as Section 1-8-113 of Title 10A, unless
16 there is created a duplication in numbering, reads as follows:
17 If there is cause to believe a crime has been committed,
18 pursuant to Sections 1111 or 1123 of Title 21 of the Oklahoma
19 Statutes, by an employee or contractor of the Department of Human
20 Services against a child who is under the legal custody,
21 supervision, or authority of the Department, the Department shall
22 exercise due diligence in ensuring action has been taken by law
23 enforcement, which may include, but shall not be limited to,
24 conducting an investigation or filing a report. The Department
